message.content:
A Bombus bifarius is a species of bumblebee commonly found in North America.
It has a fluffy, yellow and black striped body with a rounded shape.
The wings are transparent and the legs are equipped with spurs for collecting pollen.
The head is black with two large, round, compound eyes and two long antennae.
They typically grow to about 1.5 centimeters in length.
Bombus bifarius can be found in a variety of habitats, including grasslands, meadows, and forests.
They are important pollinators for many wildflowers and crops.
